        <briefdescription>
<para>Send a text message to the agent asynchronously. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>The returned future completes (with <computeroutput>void</computeroutput>) when <computeroutput>TurnComplete</computeroutput> arrives. Any streaming <computeroutput>AnswerText</computeroutput> frames received before <computeroutput>TurnComplete</computeroutput> are dispatched to <computeroutput>onAnswerText</computeroutput> on the reader thread; keep the callback short and non-blocking.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>text</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>User-turn text to send. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>onAnswerText</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Optional streaming callback invoked with (chunk, isDelta, isFinal) for each streamed chunk. Ignored when empty.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>Future completing when the turn finishes. Calling <computeroutput>future::get()</computeroutput> propagates any <ref refid="class_tryll_1_1_tryll_error" kindref="compound">TryllError</ref> reported by the server or raised locally on disconnect.</para>
</simplesect>
<parameterlist kind="exception"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername><ref refid="class_tryll_1_1_tryll_error" kindref="compound">TryllError</ref></parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Only via the returned future; never directly. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
